official_title: Concurrent resolution providing for the printing of the compilation of the social security laws.

summary.text: (LATEST SUMMARY) Provides that the compilation of the social security laws, prepared in two volumes by the Social Security Administration for the use of the Committee on Ways and Means, be printed as a House document and that five hundred additional copies be printed for the use of the House Document Room, and that two thousand additional copies be printed for the use of the Committee on Ways and Means. Provides that three thousand five hundred additional copies of Volume I and five hundred additional copies of Volume II shall be printed for the use of the Committee on Finance of the Senate.
